{
  "texts": [
    "(4.50)The k T -reality theorem 4.2 tells us that the maximally-connected massless wavefunction is always real, i.e.",
    "ψ C * n = ψ C n. This impliesρ C n ({k}, {k}) = ψ C n ({k}, {k}) + ψ C n ({k}, {-k}), (4.51)i.e.",
    "the maximally-connected density matrix is parity-even.",
    "We can then check what the consequence of this is for parity-odd n-point correlators.",
    "We have⟨ϕ(k 1) • • • ϕ(k n)⟩ ′PO ≡ ⟨ϕ(k 1) • • • ϕ(k n)⟩ ′ -⟨ϕ(-k 1) • • • ϕ(-k n)⟩ ′ 2 = 1 ρ n 2 ρ C n ({k}, {k}) -ρ C n ({k}, {-k}) 2 + factorised = 0 + factorised."
  ]
}